The move seeks to cool tensions before the legislature session begins.
title: Breakfast pe charcha? Now, DKS 'invites' Sidda for meet

author: TNN
description: A passenger on an Air India flight from Dubai to Hyderabad was apprehended by airport police following allegations of sexual harassment and leaving obscene messages. The accused, identified as Biniyam Nazar, reportedly touched a stewardess inappropriately and left offensive remarks. Authorities registered a case under relevant sections of the law.
title: Drunk Kerala techie sexually harasses cabin crew on flight

author: DWAIPAYAN GHOSH
description: A 28-year-old woman was allegedly drugged, physically assaulted, and molested for nearly an hour inside a moving car after being forced into it near Ambedkar Setu. Police found her abandoned and heavily drugged in the Maidan area and have launched an investigation, reviewing CCTV footage to trace the vehicle and its occupants.
title: Kolkata: Woman 'assaulted, molested' inside moving car for nearly an hour

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Samantha Ruth Prabhu wed Raj Nidimoru today in an intimate ceremony at Isha Yoga Centre's Linga Bhairavi Temple, attended by 30 guests. She wore a red saree. Rumors swirled after Raj's ex-wife's cryptic post; they've been linked since 2024. This follows her 2021 divorce from Naga Chaitanya.
title: Samantha Prabhu weds 'The Family Man' director Raj Nidimoru; actress shares photos

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Rajya Sabha witnessed a heated exchange between Mallikarjun Kharge and JP Nadda on the first day of the Winter Session. Kharge's reference to the "sudden exit" of former Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar drew sharp criticism from Nadda, who advised him to seek medical help for political frustrations.
title: 'Speak to a doctor': RS witnesses Kharge vs Nadda over Dhankhar's 'sudden exit' — watch

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US tariffs have slowed India's manufacturing growth to a nine-month low, impacting sales and production. While exports to other regions remain strong, new export orders saw their slowest rise in over a year. India is negotiating a trade framework with the US to address these tariff challenges, though future output expectations have dipped.
title: Trump tariffs hit India’s manufacturing sector! PMI falls to 9-month low in Nov

author: KRISHNA CHAUDHARY AND HARVEER DABAS
description: Two Booth Level Officers (BLOs) in Uttar Pradesh have died while working on electoral roll revisions, one by suicide and another from a heart attack. These incidents bring the total BLO deaths during the Special Intensive Revision (SIR) exercise to at least seven, raising concerns about workload and pressure.
title: 'Want to live, but what can I do?': UP BLO dies by suicide, another of heart attack amid ‘SIR stress’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Japanese singer Maki Otsuki's Shanghai concert was abruptly halted mid-performance due to rising diplomatic tensions between China and Japan. The incident follows remarks by Japan's prime minister regarding Taiwan, leading to Beijing's strong reaction and a wave of cultural exchange cancellations, including other Japanese artists' shows.
title: China-Japan tensions flare: Maki Otsuki's concert abruptly stopped in Shanghai — watch

author: TOI Education
description: December ushers in a calmer rhythm for schools across India as exams wind down and winter break approaches. With holidays typically falling between December 20 and 31, students look forward to Christmas festivities, year-end events and a brief pause before the new academic rush begins in January. The month brings a mix of festive charm, rest and school-level transitions.
title: December 2025 school holidays: Winter vacation, Christmas and more -- check list

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: India's economy is reportedly growing at an impressive 8.2%, yet the IMF has assigned its national accounts a 'C' grade due to methodological weaknesses. This rating highlights concerns about outdated base years, price deflators, and data granularity, sparking a debate over the accuracy of the reported growth figures.
title: Explainer: Making sense of India’s 8.2% growth - and IMF’s ‘C’ on GDP data

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold and silver futures opened strongly on Monday, buoyed by a weakening dollar, anticipated US Federal Reserve rate cuts, and a depreciating rupee. Silver futures reached a new peak, with analysts expecting continued strong momentum driven by global economic factors and currency fluctuations.
title: Gold price today: Yellow metal rises; check 24K, 22K city-wise rates

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tech mogul Elon Musk believes humanity likely lives in a simulation, citing the rapid evolution of video games from simple graphics to photorealistic experiences. He argues that if this trend continues, simulated realities will become indistinguishable from our own. Musk previously shared this 'simulation hypothesis' on Joe Rogan's podcast, suggesting our existence points to this possibility.
title: ‘High probability’: Musk suggests our reality may be simulation

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman described ChatGPT's launch as a 'scientific windfall' and a defining moment, attributing its success to scaling laws for language models.  The company is now making an aggressive infrastructure bet, partnering with industry giants like Nvidia and Oracle to build massive computing capacity, aiming to become 'people's personal AI subscription'.
title: ‘We stumbled on one giant secret’: Sam Altman on ChatGPT’s breakthrough moment

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A Mumbai businesswoman has accused senior pharmaceutical officials of holding her at gunpoint, stripping her, and taking compromising photos and videos at their Mahalaxmi office. The FIR details threats of viral dissemination and fabricated legal cases. Police have registered a case under various sections of sexual violence and criminal intimidation, initiating an investigation.
title: Mumbai shocker: Woman held at gunpoint, stripped, threatened by pharma officials

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A Deputy SP in Kerala, A. Umesh, has been suspended. Allegations of sexual assault and bribery against him emerged after a police officer's suicide. An internal inquiry found Umesh misused his position. The Home Department suspended him based on the state police chief's recommendation. This action follows a review of a special report detailing grave misconduct. Disciplinary action is pending.
title: Kerala deputy SP suspended for molesting woman in custody, taking bribes

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Shedeur Sanders made his professional home debut for the Cleveland Browns, showcasing his potential despite a loss to the 49ers. Supported by his stylish mother, Pilar, who also garnered attention, Shedeur aims to solidify his starting quarterback role. Coach Stefanski praised his commitment, highlighting his growth after his first start.
title: Shedeur Sanders’ mom stuns in proud mama style with glam game-day look

author: MARIA CRAMER
description: Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani will retain Police Commissioner Jessica S. Tisch, inheriting her extensive surveillance network, the Domain Awareness System. Despite Mamdani's past concerns about police spying and privacy, he now faces the challenge of balancing public safety with civil liberties, potentially moderating his previous stances.
title: Zohran Mamdani, a sharp critic of police surveillance, will soon oversee it

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: New England Patriots quarterback Drake Maye is electrifying fans with his stellar performance, leading the team to a dominant 10-2 record. Off the field, his wife, Ann Michael Maye, is gaining a significant following on TikTok for her fitness and lifestyle content. Their combined popularity makes them a notable NFL power couple.
title: Drake Maye buzz: Wife Ann’s viral gym photo steals spotlight as Giants clash nears

author: TNN
description: Panic erupted in Ahmedabad's Subhash Society after Rahul Soni fired six rounds following a domestic dispute with his wife. Soni arrived at his in-laws' residence, argued with his wife, and then discharged firearms outside the bungalow. Police detained Soni and seized the weapons, with no injuries reported.
title: Ahmedabad man fires six rounds at in-laws’ home after quarrel with wife

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former South African pacer Dale Steyn lauded Virat Kohli's enduring ODI relevance, highlighting his "mentally young, fresh, and hungry" approach after a match-winning 135. Steyn emphasised Kohli's vast experience and unwavering self-belief, noting the star batter's palpable excitement for playing for India, even at 37. This stellar performance powered India to a 17-run victory.
title: Vintage Virat Kohli: 'Mentally young, hungry, unstoppable' — SA great delivers powerful verdict

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: By February 2026, India's telecom authority is set to implement a SIM binding policy for messaging apps like WhatsApp, compelling users to verify their registered SIM cards continuously. This initiative is designed to thwart cyber fraud by ensuring that apps do not operate on deactivated SIMs. Additionally, web versions will automatically log users out after six hours.
title: WhatsApp to stop working without SIM: Govt's new rule; 90 days to comply

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi welcomed Vice-President C.P. Radhakrishnan to the Rajya Sabha on the first day of Winter Session, highlighting his dedication to social service and his connection with tribal communities in Jharkhand. PM Modi assured the House's cooperation, emphasizing decorum and policy over slogans, while also urging the opposition to move past recent election defeats.
title: Winter Session: PM Modi welcomes Vice-President CP Radhakrishnan as Parliament opens — Watch

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi-NCR breathes easier this year, achieving its best air quality in eight years, excluding 2020.  Average AQI and severe pollution days have significantly dropped.  PM2.5 and PM10 levels are also at their lowest since 2018.  Revised GRAP guidelines now place stricter measures under Stage III, impacting office operations.  However, allegations of data manipulation and lax enforcement have surfaced.
title: Delhi-NCR AQI 8-year best: Pollution dips between Jan and Nov; only 3 ‘severe’ days in 2025

author: SAT SINGH
description: A Haryana family seeks government help to bring home the body of Vijay Kumar Sheoran. The 29-year-old student died in the UK after a stabbing incident. His brother has written to the External Affairs Ministry for urgent assistance. The family hopes for his last rites to be performed in their village.
title: Haryana youth stabbed to death in UK: 6 arrested suspects granted bail

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Oxford University Press has declared 'rage bait' the Word of the Year 2025, citing a threefold surge in online usage. This term describes content intentionally crafted to provoke anger and boost engagement.  Its selection highlights a significant shift in how online attention, interaction, and ethics are perceived and manipulated in the digital sphere.
title: Oxford word of the year: It's ‘rage bait’ — here's what it means

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Parliament's Winter Session sees the government proposing new excise duty on tobacco and a 'Health Security–National Security Cess' for pan masala. These measures aim to maintain tax revenue post-GST compensation cess expiry, ensuring continued fiscal space for public health and national security initiatives. The shift aligns with a new 40% GST slab for demerit goods.
title: Parliament Winter Session: Govt to introduce Central Excise (Amendment) Bill 2025

author: PATHIKRIT CHAKRABORTY
description: NIA widened its probe into a "white-collar" terror network linked to the Red Fort blast, conducting searches in Jammu & Kashmir and Uttar Pradesh. The investigation focuses on a sophisticated module involving educated professionals accused of funneling funds for terror activities, with former medical faculty Dr. Shaheen Shahid among those arrested.
title: Red Fort blast probe widens: NIA raids ‘Madam Surgeon’; Lucknow home searched

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's batting coach Sitanshu Kotak firmly dismissed speculation surrounding Virat Kohli's ODI future, emphasising his current form, fitness, and crucial contributions. Kotak stated that discussions about the 2027 World Cup are premature, as the team focuses on present performance. He highlighted Kohli's recent century as proof of his continued value, assuring that the veteran remains central to India's plans.
title: 'Why talk about Kohli's future?': India coach shuts down noise; hints at 2027 WC plans

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump issued an ultimatum to Venezuela's Nicolás Maduro, offering safe passage in exchange for immediate departure. Maduro reportedly refused, demanding global amnesty and control of the armed forces, leading to collapsed talks. Trump acknowledged speaking with Maduro but offered no details, later warning of Venezuelan airspace closure amid escalating US military presence and accusations of fueling a drug crisis.
title: ‘You must leave the country now’: Trump delivers blunt ultimatum to Maduro on call

author: MIHIR TANKSALE
description: A 33-year-old cab driver was arrested for allegedly murdering his married partner in Pune and setting her body ablaze in Dharashiv district. The suspect confessed to killing the woman, who was reportedly pressuring him for marriage, to escape the relationship. He then transported her body and set it on fire.
title: Pune shocker: Cab driver kills partner over marriage pressure, burns body; arrested

author: U SUDHAKAR REDDY
title: Birder alerts about Rock Eagle Owl nest; quarrying stopped for a month

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: Anthony Davis expressed strong admiration for his former coach, JJ Redick, after facing him for the first time post-trade.  Despite the Lakers' loss to the Mavericks, Davis highlighted their enduring bond, recalling Redick's debut season as a learning experience for both.  This encounter underscored the mutual respect between the two as their NBA careers progress.
title: Anthony Davis shares heartfelt 3-word message to JJ Redick after Lakers clash

author: PTI
description: Maharashtra minister Jaykumar Gore urged women beneficiaries of the Mukhyamantri Majhi Ladki Bahin scheme to vote for Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis. Addressing a rally, Gore advised women to accept money from any source but to remember the Rs 1,500 monthly stipend, warning it would stop if Fadnavis wasn't in power. He emphasized loyalty to the CM during upcoming civic polls.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: KL Rahul expressed admiration and nerves after Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma's stellar performances secured India's 17-run victory over South Africa in the opening ODI. Kohli's 135 and Rohit's 57 anchored India's 349/8, with bowlers Harshit Rana and Kuldeep Yadav also playing crucial roles in the tense win.
title: IND vs SA: 'Virat, Rohit make oppositions look silly' — Rahul says it's fun having them around

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Ludwig Minelli, the founder of Swiss right-to-die group Dignitas, has died through an assisted death at the age of 92. Minelli, who established Dignitas in 1998, dedicated his final years to exploring new avenues for end-of-life choices. The organization will continue his legacy, upholding principles of self-determination and freedom of choice.
title: Man who fought for 'right to die' ends life through assisted death at 92

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: An xAI engineer's post about working 36 hours straight sparked debate on work-life balance. Top executive Ayush Jaiswal shifted focus, urging anger towards the systemic issues necessitating such extreme efforts rather than blaming individuals. This highlights the intense work culture often associated with Elon Musk's companies.
title: Musk’s xAI work hours row: Indian-origin exec reacts to colleague's 36-hour claim

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Nepal's central bank has awarded a contract to a Chinese firm for printing new banknotes. The company will design and supply notes of NRs 50, NRs 500, and NRs 1,000. This comes as Nepal also issued new Rs 100 notes featuring a revised map including disputed territories. The Chinese firm has prior experience printing Nepalese currency.
title: NRs 50, 500 and 1,000: Nepal awards new banknotes contract to China

author: DHIRENDRA KUMAR
description: Many fear investing due to market volatility and potential losses. However, data shows long-term equity investments typically reward patience, while inaction risks losing purchasing power to inflation. Protecting yourself with an emergency fund and insurance, then starting small with a diversified fund, helps manage fear and build wealth over time through consistent, disciplined behaviour.
title: Scared of losing money? How to start investing even when you are afraid - explained

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Monday on the back of strong domestic fundamentals and better-than-expected GDP growth numbers.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 above 26,250; BSE Sensex near 86,000

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: The National Investigation Agency (NIA) and local police conducted coordinated raids at eight locations across Delhi on Monday, including the residence of key suspect Jasir Bilal Wani. The operation is reportedly connected to a "white collar terror" network, with multiple teams conducting simultaneous searches. Further details are expected as the investigation progresses.

author: SAHIL MALHOTRA
description: Shubman Gill is set to begin his rehabilitation at the BCCI Centre of Excellence in Bengaluru from December 1. The 26-year-old, who missed the Test and ODI series against South Africa due to a neck injury, is recovering well and will start training soon. His participation in the upcoming T20I series depends on his full recovery and readiness.
title: Shubman Gill's fitness: India captain to begin rehab at CoE; likely to resume batting this week

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal Financial Services has identified Reliance Industries and HCL Tech as top stock picks for the week of December 1, 2025. RIL's strong performance in Retail and RJio, coupled with O2C earnings improvement, drives growth expectations. HCL Tech's robust deal wins and early traction in AI solutions support its upgraded services growth guidance.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for the week starting Dec 1 - check list

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Winter exacerbates autoimmune symptoms due to declining Vitamin D, disrupted melatonin, increased viral infections, and dietary/lifestyle changes. Specialists recommend Vitamin D supplementation, improved sleep hygiene, anti-inflammatory diets, and regular indoor activity to enhance resilience and reduce flare-ups during colder months.
title: Why winter worsens autoimmune symptoms, and how to prevent it

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli's match-winning century in the first ODI against South Africa sparked speculation about a potential Test comeback. However, the star batter firmly stated his commitment to playing only one format of the game. Kohli emphasised his mental approach to cricket and the importance of enjoyment in his continued success.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Cold showers can cause a sudden rise in blood pressure. This happens due to blood vessel tightening and stress hormone release. People with heart conditions face higher risks. However, the body might adapt over time to regular cold exposure. A cautious approach is advised. Gradual temperature reduction and consulting a doctor are recommended for safety.
title: Can a cold shower really spike your blood pressure?

author: VENKADESAN S
description: Cyclone Ditwah claimed three lives in Tamil Nadu due to wall collapses and electrocution, while Sri Lanka suffered a devastating toll exceeding 330. Chennai was largely spared the predicted fury, experiencing only light rain and winds. Significant damage to homes and crops occurred across Tamil Nadu, prompting calls for national calamity classification.
title: Cyclone Ditwah rampage: Tamil Nadu reports 3 deaths as storm drenches state

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A 30-year-old Indian student from Haryana, Vijay Kumar Sheoran, was fatally stabbed in Worcester, UK. He had moved to the UK for higher studies earlier this year. His family has appealed to the Ministry of External Affairs for assistance in repatriating his body for final rites.
title: Quit govt job, went to UK for studies: Haryana student stabbed to death in attack

author: TNN
description: A catastrophic crash involving two government buses in Tirupattur has led to a grim toll of 11 fatalities, among them nine women, and inflicted injuries on 54 individuals. The incident, triggered by a driver trying to dodge a pedestrian, caused a traffic standstill lasting half an hour. Chief Minister M.K.
title: Tamil Nadu bus crash: 9 women among 11 killed as 2 govt buses collide

author: GITESH SHELKE
description: A parking attendant in Kalyaninagar tragically lost his life after being hit by a car driven by a reportedly drunk IT employee. The 50-year-old techie, who was refused service at the restaurant, reversed his vehicle, lost control, and fatally struck the attendant before crashing into a wall. The incident occurred near another fatal accident site.
title: 'I’m not a bad man': Drunk Pune techie driving off in a huff runs over valet

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Nalin Haley, son of Nikki Haley, has responded to accusations of being a "nepo baby" and "spoiled brat." He defended his public statements on economic issues, asserting he receives no parental assistance and is advocating for his generation's job prospects and affordability. Critics argue his arguments are performative and ignore pressing concerns for young people.
title: 'Got zero help from parents': Nalin Haley hits back at ‘nepo baby’ jibes

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: China's booming humanoid robotics industry is facing government scrutiny over a potential investment bubble. Beijing is concerned about too many similar companies and the risk of stifling genuine innovation. This comes as the sector, recently highlighted as a key growth driver, attracts massive investment following viral robot demonstrations.
title: Robots are scaring Chinese government; the ‘reason’ is these companies; 150-plus involved

author: VEENA MANI
description: Top Indian IT firms saw a significant 70% drop in H-1B initial employment approvals for FY 2025. Tech giants like Amazon and Meta now dominate new H-1B approvals, signaling a major shift in the visa landscape. This trend suggests a focus on retaining existing employees rather than bringing in new talent.
title: Shifting visa pattern: H-1B nod for IT firms drops to 4.5k - lowest in a decade

author: TNN
description: Elon Musk stated Starlink is designed for rural areas and disaster recovery, not dense cities, due to physics limitations. He explained satellite beams are like flashlights, supporting limited users, making urban coverage impractical. Musk highlighted Starlink's role in serving underserved regions and maintaining connectivity when terrestrial infrastructure fails.
title: Starlink cannot compete with telcos in cities: Musk

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Dhanush and Kriti Sanon's 'Tere Ishq Mein' has exceeded expectations, proving its hype with a strong opening weekend. The romantic drama garnered Rs 51.75 crore in its first three days, showing a consistent upward trend in box office collections and audience reception.
title: Tere Ishk Mein box office: Dhanush-Kriti Sanon film crosses Rs 50cr mark

author: SOUMITRA BOSE
description: A 1972 rape survivor, whose case led to landmark legal reforms, was found living in dire conditions. A TOI report sparked immediate action from Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis and widespread support from across India and abroad. Authorities have pledged financial aid, housing, and rations, offering a lifeline to the woman known as 'Mathura'.
title: TOI impact: Help and hope spring for 1972 rape survivor; ‘Mathura’ to receive Rs 10 lakh aid, pension

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US President Donald Trump stated he is willing to release the results of an October MRI scan, describing them as "perfect." Trump further told reporters he has “no idea” which part of his body the MRI covered. The White House has not clarified the purpose or body part scanned, only confirming it was part of a routine physical.
title: Trump to release MRI results, but he doesn’t know which body part was scanned – watch

author: AMISHA PANDEY
description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce are reportedly planning a lavish three-day wedding celebration at Swift's Rhode Island mansion. Sources suggest the event will include multiple events, balancing intimate moments with a large guest list of around 300 people. While unconfirmed, the rumors have generated significant fan excitement for a potentially iconic, fairytale-like wedding weekend.

description: Cardi B delighted fans by sharing glimpses of Stefon Diggs' birthday. A custom Snoopy football cake, celebrating his jersey number, stole the show. This intimate peek into their celebration resonated deeply, earning them 'relationship goals' praise.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: New research suggests a link between high glycemic index (GI) diets and an increased risk of lung cancer, even in non-smokers. A large study found individuals consuming the highest GI foods had a significantly higher incidence of lung cancer. This association highlights how rapid blood sugar spikes may impact lung tissue over time, independent of traditional risk factors.

description: Sri Lanka's cricket tour of Pakistan faced security concerns after a bomb blast in Islamabad, leading to player apprehension. Extensive military security measures were implemented, ensuring the team's safety. Despite restrictions, captain Dasun Shanaka expressed gratitude to the PCB and security forces, acknowledging batting challenges and looking forward to future tours.

author: TNN
description: A 32-year-old man murdered his estranged wife at a women's hostel in Coimbatore, stabbing her to death over an alleged extramarital affair. He then took a selfie with her body and posted it on WhatsApp with a vengeful message. The accused has been arrested by the Rathinapuri police.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Yuzvendra Chahal celebrated Virat Kohli's record 52nd ODI century with enthusiastic social media posts. Kohli's masterful 135 guided India to a commanding total against South Africa. Chahal's playful messages highlighted Kohli's potential pursuit of Sachin Tendulkar's milestone, showcasing their close bond and the spinner's unfiltered joy in celebrating his "Virat bhaiya's" achievements.

author: VEENA MANI
description: Top Indian IT firms saw a significant 70% drop in H-1B initial employment approvals for FY 2025. Tech giants like Amazon and Meta now dominate new H-1B approvals, signaling a major shift in the visa landscape. This trend suggests a focus on retaining existing employees rather than bringing in new talent.
title: Shifting visa pattern: H-1B nod for IT firms drops to 4.5k - lowest in a decade

description: Parliament's winter session faces disruption as opposition demands a debate on the Special Intensive Revision of electoral rolls, alleging irregularities. Other issues like national security and air pollution were also raised.
